      "episode_title": "Is being thrifty a virtue_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "Today's consumer culture encourages us",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.966853",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"ES\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "9a9fbe79-e7a0-4a41-9ca6-5973a71b4a86",
      "chunk_index": 2,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176696",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "Is being thrifty a virtue_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "to look at the world's most important human rights emergencies. But before we discover more about that, it's time for today's quiz question. If you're trying to save money, you probably know how hard it can be. So my question is what percentage of people in the UK do you think have less than a thousand pounds in savings? Is it a. 5%, b. 15% or c. 30%? Well, if I'm anything to go by, I'd say c. 30%.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.969420",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"CI\", \"RTA\", \"ES\", \"UI\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "63e04077-55cb-4cfa-b3e5-3934b60752b4",
      "chunk_index": 3,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176696",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "Is being thrifty a virtue_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "Well, there are two dictionary definitions of thrift. The older of the two comes from the word thrive, etymologically, and describes thrift as the ability to live well and to flourish. So it's that sense of human flourishing. And the more recent definition is the one we're probably more familiar",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.971839",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"BI\", \"ES\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "fb2aaa53-d224-4d30-bb26-b9a1c99d8539",
      "chunk_index": 4,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176696",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "Is being thrifty a virtue_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "with, which is about frugality. All of that said, it's been used historically, of course, by various people in various moments, in various different places, in very different ways. And they've often had a social or religious agenda. It seems the oldest definition of thrift has nothing to do with saving money and is connected to the verbs thrive and flourish, meaning to grow or develop successfully.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.974367",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"CI\", \"VaR\", \"ES\", \"AI\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "ca8436cb-0b9b-48bd-85b9-d5505220ccb0",
      "chunk_index": 5,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176696",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "Is being thrifty a virtue_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "The Puritans believe that being frugal was a religious virtue and that people ought to save money in order to give to others in need.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.976572",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "05d3dcc2-d535-46b6-a48e-6d73de2657f4",
      "chunk_index": 6,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176696",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "Is being thrifty a virtue_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "Throughout history, then, there have been different versions of thrift. And this may be because different religions or social groups had their own agenda – a specific aim or reason for a particular group to do something. For example, the Victorian definition of thrift was based on a social agenda about being a respectable member of society.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.979223",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"CI\", \"RSI\", \"ES\", \"AI\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "7db08914-3dec-4788-908b-134c328df318",
      "chunk_index": 7,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176696",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "Is being thrifty a virtue_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "And in the post-war period, it changed again as people's wealth and standard of living increased. Here's Alison Hume again.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.981438",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"AI\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "995673bd-b6a8-4374-b503-472257edbad0",
      "chunk_index": 8,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176696",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "Is being thrifty a virtue_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "No point denying that certainly in the developed world there's been a rise in consumer capitalism. That's just a truism. But thrift hasn't declined. In modern times, people's motivation to save up and be thrifty declined once they had enough to meet their basic needs – the basic necessities needed to survive, like food, clothes and shelter and nothing extra. Alison mentions that once these basic needs were satisfied, people moved away from thrift into consumerism.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.984218",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"UI\", \"RTA\", \"ES\", \"AI\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "295df87d-732b-4531-b98e-6c3e3fd14c5d",
      "chunk_index": 9,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176696",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "Is being thrifty a virtue_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "The desire to buy luxury products which were not absolutely necessary. According to some, this created a moral slide – a decrease in the standards of behaving in good, fair and honest ways. What is worth repeating is the quiz question, though, Neil.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.986661",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"UI\", \"UX\", \"ES\", \"AI\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "bee7aa7a-493d-4c3d-a703-729fbc8a9055",
      "chunk_index": 10,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176696",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "Is being thrifty a virtue_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "OK, well today we've been talking about the changing meanings of thrift – an idea connected to frugality – being careful not to spend too much money.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.988978",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "67f5d9c5-3a34-4d07-860b-614f26875eb9",
      "chunk_index": 11,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176696",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "Is being thrifty a virtue_",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "In recent times, people's ability to meet their basic needs – the necessities for survival like food and shelter – have reduced the importance of thrift, which some believe has created a moral slide – a reduction in standards of moral behaviour.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.991382",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"BI\", \"RTA\", \"ES\"]"
    },
